title: TNFs bind their physiological receptors
description: Members of the tumour necrosis factor superfamily (TNFSF) and TNF receptor superfamily (TNFRSF) have crucial roles in both innate and adaptive immunity. These members are implicated in various acquired or genetic human diseases, ranging from septic shock to autoimmune disorders, allograft rejection and cancer (So et al. 2006).
